cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the optimization of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) since the paper focuses on pruning techniques to reduce the size of neural networks. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for detecting dead units, which could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
